The paper presents a novel approach for Question Answering (QA) tasks using a dynamic network architecture that adapts to the input and question pairs. This falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML), which are covered by cs.CL and cs.AI. The paper also introduces a bank controller that allows for discrete decision making, which is relevant to reinforcement learning and optimization, covered by cs.LG and cs.NE. Finally, the paper uses entity extraction and memory banks, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision and image processing, covered by cs.CV.
